M|traction-eos|name: traction-eos
M|traction-eos|description: 'Implement the Entrepreneurial Operating System (EOS) to align vision and execution across a company. Use when the user mentions "EOS", "V/TO", "quarterly rocks", "Level 10 meetings", "ac
M|traction-eos|license: MIT
M|traction-eos|metadata:
M|traction-eos|author: wondelai
M|traction-eos|version: "1.1.0"
M|traction-eos|A complete system for running a business with six key components. Designed for entrepreneurial companies ($2M-$50M revenue, 10-250 employees) that want to align vision and execution.
M|traction-eos|**Most businesses suffer from the same core issues: people, vision, traction.** EOS provides a simple, complete operating system that strengthens the Six Key Components of any organization.
M|traction-eos|**The foundation:** Great vision without traction is hallucination. Traction without vision is aimless. EOS connects the two through a practical, weekly operating rhythm.
M|traction-eos|**Goal: 10/10.** When evaluating or implementing business processes, rate 0-10 based on EOS component strength. A 10/10 means all six components are strong, meetings are productive, and quarterly rock
M|traction-eos|```
M|traction-eos|Vision → People → Data → Issues → Process → Traction
M|traction-eos|```
M|traction-eos|Every business is built on these six components. EOS strengthens all six.
M|traction-eos|**Question:** Does everyone in the organization know where you're going and how you plan to get there?
M|traction-eos|**Tool: Vision/Traction Organizer (V/TO)**
M|traction-eos|The V/TO answers eight questions on two pages:
M|traction-eos|| Question | What It Defines | Example |
M|traction-eos||----------|----------------|---------|
M|traction-eos|| **Core Values** | 3-7 non-negotiable beliefs | "Own it", "Do the right thing", "Grow or die" |
M|traction-eos|| **Core Focus** | Purpose/cause/passion + niche | "Simplify small business" + "Cloud accounting" |
M|traction-eos|| **10-Year Target** | Big, hairy, audacious goal | "$100M revenue" or "10,000 customers" |
M|traction-eos|| **mkt str** | Target market, 3 uniques, proven process, guarantee | Who you serve, why you're different |
M|traction-eos|| **3-Year Picture** | What company looks like in 3 years | Revenue, profit, headcount, key metrics |
M|traction-eos|| **1-Year Plan** | Revenue, profit, measurables, goals | Specific targets for this year |
M|traction-eos|| **Quarterly Rocks** | 3-7 priorities for this quarter | The most important things to accomplish in 90 days |
M|traction-eos|| **Issues List** | All unresolved obstacles | Problems, ideas, opportunities to discuss |
M|traction-eos|**Process:**
M|traction-eos|1. Leadership team completes V/TO together (2-day off-site)
M|traction-eos|2. Share with entire organization
M|traction-eos|3. rv quarterly
M|traction-eos|4. Update annually
M|traction-eos|**Key insight:** If leadership team can't agree on V/TO, you have a bigger problem. Alignment comes first.
M|traction-eos|See: [references/vto.md](references/vto.md) for V/TO templates and exercises.
M|traction-eos|**Question:** Do you have the right people in the right seats?
M|traction-eos|**Tool: Accountability Chart**
M|traction-eos|Not an org chart—an accountability chart. Defines the structure and who owns what.
M|traction-eos|**Structure:**
M|traction-eos|```
M|traction-eos|Visionary ←→ Integrator
M|traction-eos|├── Sales/mkt
M|traction-eos|├── Operations
M|traction-eos|└── fin
M|traction-eos|```
M|traction-eos|**Two key roles:**
M|traction-eos|- **Visionary:** Big ideas, culture, key relationships, creative problem solving
M|traction-eos|- **Integrator:** Runs business day-to-day, manages team, executes vision, resolves conflicts
M|traction-eos|**Rule:** One person per seat. No shared accountability.
M|traction-eos|**Tool: People Analyzer**
M|traction-eos|Evaluate every person on two dimensions:
M|traction-eos|**1. Right Person (core values fit)**
M|traction-eos|| Core Value | + (most of the time) | +/- (sometimes) | - (rarely) |
M|traction-eos||-----------|---------------------|-----------------|------------|
M|traction-eos|| Own it | + | | |
M|traction-eos|| Do the right thing | | +/- | |
M|traction-eos|| Grow or die | + | | |
M|traction-eos|**Standard:** Must be "+" on all core values. One "+/-" is a conversation. Any "-" is wrong person.
M|traction-eos|**2. Right Seat (GWC)**
M|traction-eos|- **G**et it: Understands the role
M|traction-eos|- **W**ant it: Genuinely wants the role
M|traction-eos|- **C**apacity: Has the mental, physical, emotional capacity
M|traction-eos|**Must be "yes" on all three.** If missing any one, wrong seat.
M|traction-eos|**The formula:** Right People + Right Seats = A-players
M|traction-eos|**People decisions:**
M|traction-eos|- Right person, right seat → Keep and invest in
M|traction-eos|- Right person, wrong seat → Move to right seat
M|traction-eos|- Wrong person, right seat → Coaching/exit (hardest call)
M|traction-eos|- Wrong person, wrong seat → Exit immediately
M|traction-eos|See: [references/people.md](references/people.md) for accountability chart and people analyzer templates.
M|traction-eos|**Question:** Are you managing based on objective data, or subjective opinions?
M|traction-eos|**Tool: Scorecard**
M|traction-eos|A weekly report card of 5-15 numbers that tell you how the business is doing.
M|traction-eos|**Scorecard rules:**
M|traction-eos|- Activity-based metrics (leading indicators), not results (lagging)
M|traction-eos|- Weekly numbers (monthly is too slow)
M|traction-eos|- Every number has an owner
M|traction-eos|- Every number has a goal
M|traction-eos|- Red/green: on track or off track
M|traction-eos|**Example Scorecard:**
M|traction-eos|| Metric | Owner | Goal | W1 | W2 | W3 | W4 |
M|traction-eos||--------|-------|------|----|----|----|----|
M|traction-eos|| Revenue | Sales Lead | $50K/wk | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ | ✓ |
M|traction-eos|| New Leads | mkt | 100/wk | ✓ | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ |
M|traction-eos|| Demos Completed | Sales | 20/wk | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
M|traction-eos|| Customer NPS | Support | >50 | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
M|traction-eos|| Cash Balance | fin | >$200K | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
M|traction-eos|**Benefits:**
M|traction-eos|- Spot problems 2-4 weeks earlier
M|traction-eos|- Reduce "gut feeling" management
M|traction-eos|- Create accountability without micromanagement
M|traction-eos|- Everyone knows the score
M|traction-eos|**Metric selection:** If you had to go on vacation for 4 weeks, what 5-15 numbers would tell you how the business is doing?
M|traction-eos|See: [references/data.md](references/data.md) for scorecard templates and metric selection.
M|traction-eos|**Question:** Are you identifying, discussing, and solving issues quickly?
M|traction-eos|**Tool: Issues Solving Track (IDS)**
M|traction-eos|**I**dentify → **D**iscuss → **S**olve
M|traction-eos|**Step 1: Identify**
M|traction-eos|- What's the real issue? (Not the symptom)
M|traction-eos|- Ask "Why?" until you reach root cause
M|traction-eos|- State the issue in one sentence
M|traction-eos|**Step 2: Discuss**
M|traction-eos|- Everyone gets input (not equal time)
M|traction-eos|- Tangents are stopped
M|traction-eos|- Focus on the ONE issue
M|traction-eos|- Time-boxed (usually 5-15 minutes)
M|traction-eos|**Step 3: Solve**
M|traction-eos|- dec is made
M|traction-eos|- Action items are assigned (who + what + when)
M|traction-eos|- Move to next issue
M|traction-eos|**Three types of issues:**
M|traction-eos|| Type | Examples | Action |
M|traction-eos||------|----------|--------|
M|traction-eos|| **Problems** | Customer churn, team conflict, system outage | IDS → solve |
M|traction-eos|| **Ideas** | New feature, process change, market opportunity | IDS → decide (yes/no/later) |
M|traction-eos|| **Obstacles** | Blocking a rock, resource constraint, dependency | IDS → remove or escalate |
M|traction-eos|**Issues list rules:**
M|traction-eos|- Everyone can add issues
M|traction-eos|- Prioritize: most important first
M|traction-eos|- Not all issues get solved every meeting
M|traction-eos|- Unsolved issues carry forward
M|traction-eos|**Common IDS mistakes:**
M|traction-eos|- Discussing symptoms, not root cause
M|traction-eos|- Rehashing same issue every week
M|traction-eos|- No clear action items
M|traction-eos|- Too much discussion, not enough solving
M|traction-eos|See: [references/issues.md](references/issues.md) for IDS facilitation guides.
M|traction-eos|**Question:** Have you documented and consistently followed your core processes?
M|traction-eos|**Tool: Core Process Documentation**
M|traction-eos|**The 20/80 rule:** doc 20% of your processes to get 80% consistency.
M|traction-eos|**Identify core processes:**
M|traction-eos|- HR process (hiring, onboarding, reviews)
M|traction-eos|- Sales process (lead → close)
M|traction-eos|- Operations process (delivery, fulfillment)
M|traction-eos|- Customer service process (support → resolution)
M|traction-eos|- fin process (invoicing, collections)
M|traction-eos|**Documentation format:**
M|traction-eos|1. Name the process
M|traction-eos|2. List 5-20 major steps
M|traction-eos|3. Add just enough detail (not a 50-page manual)
M|traction-eos|4. Make it visual where possible
M|traction-eos|**Example: Sales Process "The Closer"**
M|traction-eos|1. Qualify lead (BANT: Budget, Authority, Need, Timeline)
M|traction-eos|2. Discovery call (30 min, use question guide)
M|traction-eos|3. Demo (customize to their pain points)
M|traction-eos|4. Proposal (send within 24 hours)
M|traction-eos|5. Follow up (3 touches in 7 days)
M|traction-eos|6. Close or disqualify
M|traction-eos|**Followed By All (FBA):**
M|traction-eos|- doc it
M|traction-eos|- Train on it
M|traction-eos|- Measure compliance
M|traction-eos|- Update quarterly
M|traction-eos|See: [references/process.md](references/process.md) for process documentation templates.
M|traction-eos|**Question:** Are you executing on your vision every day?
M|traction-eos|**Two tools: Rocks and Level 10 Meetings**
M|traction-eos|**Definition:** The 3-7 most important things to accomplish in the next 90 days.
M|traction-eos|**Why 90 days?**
M|traction-eos|- Long enough to accomplish something meaningful
M|traction-eos|- Short enough to maintain urgency
M|traction-eos|- Natural human rhythm for focus
M|traction-eos|**Rock-setting process:**
M|traction-eos|1. rv V/TO (vision, 3-year, 1-year)
M|traction-eos|2. Brainstorm: "What must get done this quarter to stay on track?"
M|traction-eos|3. Narrow to 3-7 company rocks
M|traction-eos|4. Assign each rock to one owner
M|traction-eos|5. Each leadership member also has 3-7 individual rocks
M|traction-eos|6. Share with entire organization
M|traction-eos|7. Track weekly
M|traction-eos|**SMART rocks:**
M|traction-eos|- **S**pecific: "Launch new pricing page" not "improve pricing"
M|traction-eos|- **M**easurable: Clear completion criteria
M|traction-eos|- **A**chievable: Can be done in 90 days
M|traction-eos|- **R**ealistic: Given current resources
M|traction-eos|- **T**ime-bound: Due end of quarter
M|traction-eos|**Rock scoring:**
M|traction-eos|- **Done** = checked off (no partial credit)
M|traction-eos|- **Not done** = carried forward or dropped
M|traction-eos|- **Goal:** 80%+ completion rate
M|traction-eos|**Anti-patterns:**
M|traction-eos|- Too many rocks (>7) → Focus is diluted
M|traction-eos|- Rocks too vague → Can't tell if done
M|traction-eos|- No owner → Nobody accountable
M|traction-eos|- All rocks are "business as usual" → Not moving the needle
M|traction-eos|See: [references/rocks.md](references/rocks.md) for rock-setting exercises.
M|traction-eos|**The most important meeting in EOS.** Runs every week, same day, same time, same agenda.
M|traction-eos|**Duration:** 90 minutes, never longer.
M|traction-eos|**Agenda:**
M|traction-eos|| Time | Section | Purpose |
M|traction-eos||------|---------|---------|
M|traction-eos|| 5 min | **Segue** | Good news (personal and professional) |
M|traction-eos|| 5 min | **Scorecard** | rv weekly numbers |
M|traction-eos|| 5 min | **Rock rv** | On track / Off track for each rock |
M|traction-eos|| 5 min | **Customer/Employee Headlines** | Quick updates |
M|traction-eos|| 5 min | **To-Do List** | rv last week's to-dos (done or not done) |
M|traction-eos|| 60 min | **IDS** | Identify, Discuss, Solve issues |
M|traction-eos|| 5 min | **Conclude** | Recap to-dos, rate meeting 1-10 |
M|traction-eos|**Level 10 meeting rules:**
M|traction-eos|- Starts on time, ends on time (non-negotiable)
M|traction-eos|- Same day, same time every week
M|traction-eos|- No phones/laptops (except for agenda)
M|traction-eos|- IDS gets 60 of 90 minutes (most important part)
M|traction-eos|- Rate meeting 1-10 at end (target: 8+)
M|traction-eos|- If below 8, discuss what to improve
M|traction-eos|**Why "Level 10"?**
M|traction-eos|- Every meeting is rated 1-10 by participants
M|traction-eos|- Goal is to consistently achieve 10/10
M|traction-eos|**To-Do rules:**
M|traction-eos|- 7-day action items only
M|traction-eos|- Each has owner and due date
M|traction-eos|- Done = 100% complete
M|traction-eos|- 90%+ completion rate is target
M|traction-eos|See: [references/level-10.md](references/level-10.md) for meeting facilitation guides.
M|traction-eos|**Typical rollout: 2 years to full implementation**
M|traction-eos|| Phase | Timeline | Focus |
M|traction-eos||-------|----------|-------|
M|traction-eos|| **Focus Day** | Day 1 (8 hours) | Accountability chart, rocks, scorecard, Level 10 |
M|traction-eos|| **Vision Building Day 1** | Month 1 | V/TO: core values, core focus, 10-year target |
M|traction-eos|| **Vision Building Day 2** | Month 2 | V/TO: mkt str, 3-year, 1-year, rocks |
M|traction-eos|| **Quarterly Sessions** | Every 90 days | rv rocks, set new rocks, IDS major issues |
M|traction-eos|| **Annual Planning** | Yearly | Full V/TO rv, set 1-year plan, Q1 rocks |
M|traction-eos|**Self-implementation vs. EOS Implementer:**
M|traction-eos|- Self: Read the book, follow the tools (free, slower)
M|traction-eos|- EOS Implementer: Certified facilitator guides the process (faster, expensive)
M|traction-eos|Rate your company 1-5 on each statement:
M|traction-eos|| Component | Statement | Score (1-5) |
M|traction-eos||-----------|-----------|-------------|
M|traction-eos|| **Vision** | Leadership team is on the same page with where we're going and how to get there | |
M|traction-eos|| **People** | We have the right people in the right seats | |
M|traction-eos|| **Data** | We manage from a weekly scorecard of 5-15 numbers | |
M|traction-eos|| **Issues** | We solve issues quickly and permanently | |
M|traction-eos|| **Process** | Core processes are documented and followed by all | |
M|traction-eos|| **Traction** | We set and achieve 90-day priorities (rocks) | |
M|traction-eos|**Scoring:**
M|traction-eos|- 25-30: Strong (maintain and fine-tune)
M|traction-eos|- 20-24: Good (close gaps)
M|traction-eos|- 15-19: Average (significant work needed)
M|traction-eos|- Below 15: Weak (consider EOS implementer)
M|traction-eos|| Mistake | Why It Fails | Fix |
M|traction-eos||---------|-------------|------|
M|traction-eos|| **Skipping Level 10s** | Lose weekly rhythm, issues pile up | Protect meeting, never cancel |
M|traction-eos|| **Too many rocks** | No focus, nothing gets done | Max 7 company rocks, 3-7 per person |
M|traction-eos|| **Vague rocks** | Can't tell if done | Write SMART rocks with clear criteria |
M|traction-eos|| **No scorecard** | Managing by gut, surprises | Choose 5-15 weekly numbers |
M|traction-eos|| **Wrong people kept** | Drags entire team down | Use People Analyzer, make tough calls |
M|traction-eos|| **V/TO not shared** | Team doesn't know the vision | Share with entire company |
M|traction-eos|Audit any business:
M|traction-eos|| Question | If No | Action |
M|traction-eos||----------|-------|--------|
M|traction-eos|| Does leadership agree on vision? | Misalignment | Complete V/TO together |
M|traction-eos|| Right people in right seats? | Performance issues | People Analyzer on all seats |
M|traction-eos|| Managing from data weekly? | Reactive management | Build weekly scorecard |
M|traction-eos|| Issues solved permanently? | Same problems repeat | Implement IDS in Level 10s |
M|traction-eos|| Core processes documented? | Inconsistency | doc top 5 processes |
M|traction-eos|| 90-day priorities set and tracked? | No traction | Set quarterly rocks |
